    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `nvim -u NORC`, the following zsh code (expected indentation)\n\n```\nfunction test() {                           \n  echo 1 \\                                  \n    && echo 2                               \n}                                           \necho 3\n```\n\nwould be reindented to (unexpected indentation)\n\n```\nfunction test() {                           \n  echo 1 \\                                  \n    && echo 2                               \n  }                                         \n  echo 3 \n```\n\nand with `nvim --clean`, it would be\n\n```\nfunction test() {                           \n        echo 1 \\                                                                        \n                && echo 2                                                               \n}                                           \necho 3 \n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim -u NORC test.zsh # paste and indent above code`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCorrect bracket `{` indentation after continuation line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.37.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
